3
i, k, q
1 \le k \le i \le q
\frac{{\left( {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {q - k}\\ {i - k} \end{array}} \right)}}{{\left( {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} q\\ i \end{array}} \right)}} = \frac{{\left( {i - k + 1} \right) \cdot \left( {i - k + 2} \right) \cdot ... \cdot \left( i \right)}}{{\left( {q - k + 1} \right) \cdot \left( {q - k + 2} \right) \cdot ... \cdot \left( q \right)}} \le \frac{{{i^k}}}{{{q^k}}}
{\left( {i - k + 1} \right) \cdot \left( {i - k + 2} \right) \cdot ... \cdot \left( i \right) \le {i^k}}
{\left( {q - k + 1} \right) \cdot \left( {q - k + 2} \right) \cdot ... \cdot \left( q \right) \le {q^k}}
k=4
